page.title: 09HOUSING
page.content:
The bulk of the population of this block reside in 4 hamlets/villages but with scattered housing and farms throughout.
The houses range from old to fairly modern.
Most are red brick though some are timber framed. White is a popular colour. No thatched houses were found and no flat roofed ones, rather all were gabled. Most have tiles on their rooves but some have slate.
36% were semi-detached 0% were terraced 57% were 2 storeyed 7% were cottages 36% were bungalows 0% were tower blocks 0% were mobile homes
